{{see|Job}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From ''job of work'' "chunk of work", from {{F.}} ''[[gobet]]'' "a [[bite]]", from ''[[gober]]'' "to devour".

===Pronunciation===
*jŏb, /dʒɒb/, /<tt>dZQb</tt>/
*{{audio|en-us-job.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɒb|Rhymes: -ɒb]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#A [[task]].
#:''I've got a job for you - could you wash the dishes?''
#An economic role for which a person is paid.
#:''His job is as a plumber.''

